# Day 2: Cloud Models (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS) + IBM Cloud Overview

## Cloud Service Models

- **IaaS (Infrastructure as a Service):**  
  Renting virtual hardware like servers and storage.  
  *Example:* AWS EC2, Google Compute Engine.

- **PaaS (Platform as a Service):**  
  Renting platforms to build and run your apps without managing hardware.  
  *Example:* AWS Elastic Beanstalk, Google App Engine.

- **SaaS (Software as a Service):**  
  Using ready-made software hosted on the cloud.  
  *Example:* Gmail, Dropbox, Microsoft 365.

## IBM Cloud Overview

IBM Cloud offers cloud services similar to AWS and GCP, focusing on hybrid cloud and AI tools.
